To build and install lgmon:

        for rpm
        ./autogen.sh --program-suffix=<Printer Model Name>
        for deb
        ./autogen.sh --prefix=/usr --enable-progpath=/usr/bin --program-suffix=<Printer Model Name>
        make
        make install

To build and install lgmon with AUTOCONF

You can set the following <Printer Model Name>.
            ip7200
            mp230
            mg2200
            mg3200
            mg4200
            mg5400
            mg6300
            e510

Example for building the mg6300 lgmon with the new automake and autoconf:
        for rpm
        ./autogen.sh --program-suffix=mg6300
        for deb
        ./autogen.sh --prefix=/usr --enable-progpath=/usr/bin --program-suffix=mg6300
        make
        make install

